problems.title: Two Sum
problems.note: Brute Force or Two-pass Hash Table

problems.title: Add Two Numbers
problems.note: Keep track of the carry using a variable and simulate digits-by-digits sum starting from the head of list, which contains the least-significant digit.

problems.title: Longest Palindromic Substring
problems.note: avoid unnecessary re-computation while validating palindromes. Consider the case ababa. If we already knew that bab is a palindrome, it is obvious that ababa must be a palindrome since the two left and right end letters are the same.
